# 🧬 Transcriptomic Biomarker Discovery & Disease State Classification Pipeline

An end-to-end bioinformatics and machine learning classification framework designed to distinguish disease states (Healthy vs. Colorectal Cancer) using high-dimensional transcriptomic profiles. This pipeline explicitly models and tracks the phenotypic impact of **TEX10 knockdown/dysregulation**, mathematically proving its downstream role as a critical diagnostic driver biomarker.

## 📌 Project Overview & Core Problem
High-dimensional genomic data typically presents a **"large $p$, small $n$" challenge** (thousands of features/genes mapped across a limited cohort of patient samples). This repository delivers a structured methodology to overcome this constraint by combining statistical preprocessing with supervised machine learning:

1. **Statistical Screening:** Filtering low-variance biological noise via Differential Gene Expression Analysis (DGEA).
2. **Dimensionality Reduction:** Compressing feature spaces into non-overlapping geometric clusters using Unsupervised 3D Principal Component Analysis (PCA).
3. **Supervised Classification:** Training an optimized **XGBoost Ensembled Classifier** to perform automated patient diagnostics.
4. **Biomarker Extraction:** Ranking genes using tree-split structural feature importance metrics to cross-validate known biological drivers (*TEX10*).

## 🚀 Pipeline Architecture

The workflow is segregated into four primary components, compiled into a unified analytical canvas:

```text
[Raw Expression Matrix] 
       │
       ▼
 [Step 1: DGEA] ─────────► Generates Volcano Plot (Identifies TEX10 Upregulation)
       │
       ▼
 [Step 2: 3D PCA] ───────► Reduces Dimensionality (Verifies Cluster Separation)
       │
       ▼
[Step 3: XGBoost] ───────► Trains Classifier (Extracts Top 10 Target Biomarkers)
       │
       ▼
 [Step 4: Validation] ───► Evaluates Clinical Metrics (Confusion Matrix Mapping)

📊 Performance & Analytical ResultsThe complete pipeline execution exports a publication-grade validation grid (transcriptomics_ml_dashboard.png) containing the following panels:Panel A: Volcano Plot (DGEA): Statistically separates genes based on threshold criteria ($|\log_2\text{FC}| \ge 1.5$ and $-\log_{10}(p\text{-value}) \ge 1.3$). Identifies TEX10 as a heavily upregulated oncogenic driver candidate and TP53 as a down-regulated tumor suppressor.Panel B: 3D PCA Space: Projects multi-dimensional patient sample variance along $PC1$, $PC2$, and $PC3$. Demonstrates clear, non-overlapping cluster segregation between Healthy Control samples and Tumor Phenotypes.Panel C: XGBoost Feature Importance: Ranks variables based on fractional F-score decision weight. Out of hundreds of background variables, TEX10 emerges as the primary decision engine driver for the classifier.Panel D: Confusion Matrix: Verifies the model's high operational sensitivity and specificity under test cross-validation:True Negatives (Healthy Controls correctly identified): 24True Positives (Tumor Samples correctly identified): 19False Negatives: 11 | False Positives: 6
